(Status: Alpha documentation snapshot \(2026-03-12\).) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(This document explains how witness data is handled, how block/tx size is measured, and how to) Tj
T*
(estimate TPS from real chain data.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Canonical limits) Tj
T*
(From Src/Utility/const.py:) Tj
T*
(- MAX_BLOCK_SIZE_BYTES = 2,500,000 \(base-byte ceiling\)) Tj
T*
(- MAX_BLOCK_WEIGHT = 10,000,000) Tj
T*
(- MAX_TRANSACTION_SIZE_BYTES = 250,000 \(applied as max tx vsize\)) Tj
T*
(- WITNESS_SCALE_FACTOR = 4) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Witness model) Tj
T*
(- Witness fields:) Tj
T*
(- top-level signature, pubkey, witness) Tj
T*
(- per-input script_sig) Tj
T*
(- Base transaction:) Tj
T*
(- witness removed at top-level) Tj
T*
(- inputs[].script_sig blanked) Tj
T*
(- Hashing:) Tj
T*
(- txid = no-witness hash) Tj
T*
(- wtxid = full hash) Tj
T*
(- Block commitment:) Tj
T*
(- block header carries witness_commitment when witnesses are present) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Wire encoding) Tj
T*
(- Witness signature and pubkey are canonical base64 on wire.) Tj
T*
(- Internal verification uses decoded hex/bytes.) Tj
T*
(- Legacy hex witness wire is disabled by default \(WITNESS_WIRE_ALLOW_HEX_LEGACY = False\).) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Exact size formulas) Tj
T*
(- weight = base_bytes * 3 + total_bytes) Tj
T*
(- vsize = ceil\(weight / 4\)) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(vsize is the canonical policy metric for:) Tj
T*
(- tx fee floor,) Tj
T*
(- tx size acceptance,) Tj
T*
(- mempool admission,) Tj
T*
(- miner selection.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Why logs show multiple size fields) Tj
T*
(Transaction logs include:) Tj
T*
(- size_bytes \(canonical vsize used by fee policy\),) Tj
T*
(- size_base_bytes,) Tj
T*
(- weight,) Tj
T*
(- vsize \(same policy value as size_bytes\).) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(So for policy/TPS planning, use vsize.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
